**About** - This is my first map. Made it like 3 years ago. Doesn't mean it's bad. This is my most played dodgeball map. Hope you enjoy it!

**Bugs** - When you turn your flashlight on it cuts the map in half and shows you the skybox. I have no idea what thats all about.

**Requirements** - Server running a dodgeball script. Map will not work without one.

**Cool Features** - After 30 seconds or so the map pushes everyone out of spawn to stop AFKers and whatnot. 

**Future Version Plans** - I'm planning on creating a bunch of maps using this as a template. Having different textures and scenes in the background.

**Installation** - Extract map file to Steam\steamapps\USERNAME\counter-strike source\cstrike\maps

Second TaskKnives map I've made. First one wasn't good enough to submit.

Map is pretty straight forward, you fight in the middle. The outside edges of the map are a func_push so you get pushed around in a circle at a pretty fast speed. The ramps can be used to launch yourself into the air (gain access to the spawn area). The edges also have water so you won't take damage from the fall after you jump off a ramp. It's knives only. Cell shading is nice, gives it a cartoon look.

If you change sv_airaccelerate to something higher around 400 or 500 the map is much more enjoyable.

Tip on getting back up to the spawn area: Go along the push area on the outer ring of the map. When you see the ramp coming, jump just before it so you land halfway up the ramp and then instantly jump again and you will have enough speed and height to get into the spawn area.

This is the first and likely the last version of this simple yet unique KA map of mine, created for the n00bshack clan's server. (63.209.36.84:27015, n00bshack.com) Basically there's 4 ramps, 2 across from eachother with 3 smaller platforms and 2 across from eachother with 2 larger ones. Each team has a chance of spawning on 1 of the 2 sides for both type of ramp. (ct's spawn on 1 half of the 3 platform and T's spawn on the other.) All of the other times they will spawn on ground level. There is 4 arrows on ground level pointing to the ramps, these are boosts to help you make it up to the platforms, this is where the strategy comes in. I've seen many knife maps where it's just an open arena, with this map I was going for more of a strategic ka map, basically you can camp on a high platform waiting for someone to launch up at you, or you can dive down at them from the top, or even charge up from the bottom, the possibilities are endless. To make it to the top platform you need to jump off of the boost. It includes a bit of a 3D feel, when inside of the level you can't really tell where the grass ends off, but when in the air speccing you can clearly see the end of the grass and beginning of skybox. I added trees outside for a more natural feel, like a random outdoor arena where your surrounded by glass. I dunno. lol. I would prefer you tried out in-game previous to assessment seeing as it is more based around Gameplay than anything. If you can't that is fine. Also, if someone could make me a video I'd love them. My FRAPS is being extremely slow lately, whenever I activate it I get 5 FPS.

This map was fun to make. ive put many hours into the making of this. hope you enjoy.

ive hidden other weapons as well, awps deagle scout grenade and m4a1 can all be found in this map. (most backstage)
